{
"project_context": {
"name": "Kaleidoscope",
"deployment": "Dockerized microservices via SSH, with external DB and Cloudinary",
"ci_cd": "GitHub Actions"
},
"rules": [
"When orchestrating deployments, ALWAYS verify the Git working tree is clean after committing.",
"Do not assume CI/CD finishes instantly. If the GitHub CLI ('gh') is unavailable to poll action status, explicitly pause and ask the user to confirm CI/CD success before proceeding.",
"Before running stress tests, ALWAYS verify the health of the target services (e.g., check 'docker ps' or ping the backend health endpoint).",
"Acknowledge that external services (Database, Cloudinary) rely strictly on the local '.env' file. Ensure test scripts load this file via 'python-dotenv'.",
"At the end of any automated test run, provide the user with explicit, copy-pasteable terminal commands to manually cross-verify the results in the database or logs."
]
}
